stylometry: When waiting in lines, the managers have to decide if one line with X amount of servers and the next costomer will go to the next available server is better than X amount of lines and one server in each line. The costs to consider are. Are the lines too long that its turning customers away. Is the queue time for customers affecting potential revenue? Is the wait of the line costing their customers money? The objective is to figure out which line is better suitable for the situation. In alot of senarios it is the one line of X amount of servers, becuase the wait time for the costomers is lower than the wait time of X amoumt of lines and 1 server.
